.TH "libnvme_scan_tls_keys" 9 "libnvme_scan_tls_keys" "April 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
libnvme_scan_tls_keys \- Iterate over TLS keys in a keyring
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" libnvme_scan_tls_keys
.BI "(struct libnvme_global_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "const char *keyring "  ","
.BI "libnvme_scan_tls_keys_cb_t cb "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
struct libnvme_global_ctx object
.IP "keyring" 12
Keyring holding TLS keys
.IP "cb" 12
Callback function
.IP "data" 12
Pointer for data to be passed to \fIcb\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Iterates \fIkeyring\fP and call \fIcb\fP for each TLS key. When \fIkeyring\fP is NULL
the default '.nvme' keyring is used.
A TLS key must be of type 'psk' and the description must be of the
form 'NVMe<0|1><R|G>0<1|2> <identity>', otherwise it will be skipped
during iteration.
.SH "RETURN"
Number of keys for which \fIcb\fP was called, or negative error code
